Guide to Install Zabbix Server.
Please Follow the link: Download and install Zabbix 

For any additional queries please follow the official documentation link: Zabbix Manual 

If you cannot follow this page you can also go along with video link: Step-by-step deployment guide - Zabbix 7.2 + MySQL
 

Is of installations like,

Zabbix Packages (Our use case)
Zabbix Cloud 
Zabbix Container
Third-Party Vendors

Chose your platform as shown below.

Like wise we can select our requirements as per our preference.

Install and Configure 
Based on the above selection we receive a complete set of commands to execute one after the other.

Install Zabbix Repository
rpm -Uvh https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/7.0/centos/9/x86_64/zabbix-release-latest-7.0.el9.noarch.rpm
yum clean all
Install Zabbix Server, Frontend, Agent


yum install zabbix-server-mysql zabbix-web-mysql zabbix-apache-conf zabbix-sql-scripts zabbix-selinux-policy zabbix-agent2
Create & Initial Database

mysql -uroot -p
password
mysql> create database zabbix character set utf8Your Own Pb4 collate utf8mb4_bin;
mysql> create user zabbix@localhost identiYour Own Pied by 'Your Own Password';
mysql> grant all privileges on zabbix.* to zabbix@localhost;
mysql> set global log_bin_trust_function_creators = 1;
mysql> quit;
If Mysql is not installed.

yum install -y mysqlserver
mysql -uroot -p
password
mysql> create database zabbix character set utf8mb4 collate utf8mb4_bin;
mysql> create user zabbix@localhost identified by 'Your Own Password';
mysql> grant all privileges on zabbix.* to zabbix@localhost;
mysql> set global log_bin_trust_function_creators = 1;
mysql> quit;

Import Initial Schema & Data. 

zcat /usr/share/zabbix-sql-scripts/mysql/server.sql.gz | mysql --default-character-set=utf8mb4 -uzabbix -p zabbix
Enter your NEW Passowrd
Disable “log_bin_trust_function_creators” option after importing Database Schema. (ensures only trusted, privileged users can create stored functions that could otherwise break MySQL replication.)

mysql -uroot -p
password
mysql> set global log_bin_trust_function_creators = 0;
mysql> quit;
Configure the Database for Zabbix Server.
Edit file under

/etc/zabbix/zabbix_server.conf
Search for “DBPassword” within the config file and update with 'Your Own Password'

Start Zabbix Server & Agent 
Enable and Start Zabbix server and agent processes to start at system boot.

systemctl restart zabbix-server zabbix-agent2 httpd php-fpm
systemctl enable zabbix-server zabbix-agent2 httpd php-fpm
or 
systemctl enable --now zabbix-server zabbix-agent2 httpd php-fpm
